  "prompt": "Are there any animes similar to Full Metal Alchemist brotherhood?",
  "response": "If you enjoyed **Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood**, you might appreciate the following anime series that share similar themes such as deep storytelling, well-developed characters, intricate world-building, and a blend of action, adventure, and emotional moments:\n\n1. **Hunter \u00d7 Hunter (2011)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Follows Gon Freecss as he strives to become a Hunter and find his father. The series is renowned for its complex characters, strategic battles, and evolving story arcs.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Like FMA: Brotherhood, it offers deep character development, a richly constructed world, and a balance of action and emotional depth.\n\n2. **Code Geass: Lelouch of the Rebellion**\n   - **Synopsis:** Centers on Lelouch Lamperouge, who gains the power of Geass and leads a rebellion against a powerful empire to seek revenge and create a better world.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Features political intrigue, moral dilemmas, and a protagonist with a strong sense of justice, much like Edward and Alphonse Elric\u2019s journey.\n\n3. **Attack on Titan (Shingeki no Kyojin)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Humanity battles giant humanoid Titans that threaten their existence, uncovering dark secrets about their world and the origin of the Titans.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Shares intense action, complex plot twists, and themes of sacrifice and survival.\n\n4. **D.Gray-man**\n   - **Synopsis:** Follows Allen Walker, an exorcist fighting against the Millennium Earl and his Akuma using a powerful substance called Innocence.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Incorporates themes of alchemy-like powers, deep backstories, and a battle between good and evil forces.\n\n5. **Fate/Zero**\n   - **Synopsis:** Chronicles the Fourth Holy Grail War, where mages summon heroic spirits to compete for the ultimate prize\u2014 the Holy Grail.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Offers intricate world-building, moral ambiguity, and strategic battles, akin to the complex narratives in FMA: Brotherhood.\n\n6. **Steins;Gate**\n   - **Synopsis:** Follows Rintaro Okabe, a self-proclaimed mad scientist, as he discovers time travel and faces unforeseen consequences.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** While more sci-fi, it provides a tightly woven plot, emotional depth, and character-driven storytelling.\n\n7. **Fullmetal Alchemist (2003)**\n   - **Synopsis:** An earlier adaptation of Hiromu Arakawa\u2019s manga, focusing on the Elric brothers\u2019 quest to restore their bodies after a failed alchemy experiment.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Shares the same core story and themes, though **Brotherhood** covers the manga more faithfully.\n\n8. **Magi: The Labyrinth of Magic**\n   - **Synopsis:** Follows Aladdin, Alibaba, and Morgiana as they explore dungeons, seek treasures, and unravel the mysteries of their world.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Combines adventure, magic systems, and political intrigue with rich character development.\n\n9. **Death Note**\n   - **Synopsis:** A high school student, Light Yagami, gains a notebook that can kill anyone by writing their name in it, leading to a cat-and-mouse game with detective L.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Features intense moral questions, strategic battles of wits, and a gripping narrative.\n\n10. **The Promised Neverland**\n    - **Synopsis:** Children at an orphanage discover a dark secret about their existence and plan an escape to survive.\n    - **Why It\u2019s Similar:** Provides suspenseful storytelling, deep emotional moments, and themes of sacrifice and survival.\n\nThese series each bring something unique while capturing elements that made **Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood** beloved by many. Whether you're looking for intricate plots, emotional depth, or thrilling action, there's likely something on this list that will resonate with you.",
